sp:A"}, {"#tail": ", the\n\t\t\t\tamount allowed for tenant-paid utilities shall not exceed the appropriate\n\t\t\t\tutility allowance for the family unit size as determined by the public housing\n\t\t\t\tagency regardless of the size of the dwelling unit leased by the family.", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "(B)", "@value": "United States Housing Act of 1937/s:8/ss:o/p:2/sp:B"}], "#text": "In determining the\n\t\t\t\tmonthly assistance payment for a family under ", "@display-inline": "yes-display-inline"}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n              ", "#text": "(i)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n              ", "#text": "In\n\t\t\t\tgeneral"}, "#text": "\n              ", "@id": "H28C1C41AA5574CC19A6F4E1FE23CEA59"}, {"#tail": "\n          ", "text": {"#tail": "\n            ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": {"#tail": ", upon request\n\t\t\t\tby a family that includes a person with disabilities, an elderly family, or a\n\t\t\t\tfamily that includes any person who is less than 18 years of age, the public\n\t\t\t\thousing agency shall approve a utility allowance that is higher than the\n\t\t\t\tapplicable amount on the utility allowance schedule, except that in the case of\n\t\t\t\ta family that includes a person with disabilities, the agency shall approve\n\t\t\t\tsuch higher amount only if a higher utility allowance is needed as a reasonable\n\t\t\t\taccommodation to make the program accessible to and usable by the family member\n\t\t\t\twith a disability.", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "subparagraph (A)", "@value": "United States Housing Act of 1937/s:8/ss:o/p:2/sp:A"}, "#text": "Notwithstanding "}, "enum": {"#tail": "\n              ", "#text": "(ii)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n              ", "#text": "Exception for\n\t\t\t\tcertain families"}, "#text": "\n              ", "@id": "H2A09AB9591E24F9CA2522E38C580B3B6"}], "enum": {"#tail": "\n            ", "#text": "(D)"}, "header": {"#tail": "\n            ", "#text": "Utility\n\t\t\t\tallowance"}, "#tex